						 THIS TOPIC APPLIES TO:   SQL Server (Linux only) Azure SQL Database Azure SQL Data Warehouse Parallel Data Warehouse  You can configure a SQL Server Always On Availability Group (AG) for read-scale workloads on Linux. There are two types of architectures for AGs. A architecture for high availability uses a cluster manager to provide improved business continuity. This architecture also can include read-scale replicas. To create the high-availability architecture, see  Configure SQL Server Always On Availability Group for high availability on Linux . The other architecture sup